tasks.description:
Convert the GitHub plugin (src/plugins/github.ts) to use the new function-based API.

Change from:
```
const github: PluginDef = { name: 'github', ... };
export default github;
```

To:
```
import type { DriplinePluginAPI } from '../plugin/api.js';

export default function(dl: DriplinePluginAPI) {
  dl.setName('github');
  dl.setVersion('0.1.0');
  dl.setConnectionSchema({ token: { type: 'string', required: false, description: 'GitHub PAT' } });

  // Shared auth header builder
  function authHeaders(config: Record<string, any>) { ... }

  dl.registerTable('github_repos', { ... });
  dl.registerTable('github_issues', { ... });
  dl.registerTable('github_pull_requests', { ... });
  dl.registerTable('github_stargazers', { ... });
}
```

The key benefit: shared helper functions (authHeaders, getQual) are naturally scoped inside the plugin function closure. Connection config access is cleaner.

All existing behavior must be preserved. All existing tests must still pass.

Create the plugin installer in src/plugin/installer.ts. This handles `dripline install` and `dripline remove` for npm, git, and local plugins.

Implement:

`parsePluginSource(source: string): { type: 'npm' | 'git' | 'local', name: string, ref?: string, url?: string, path?: string }` — parse install source strings:
- `npm:@dripline/github@1.0.0` → { type: 'npm', name: '@dripline/github', ref: '1.0.0' }
- `npm:dripline-plugin-aws` → { type: 'npm', name: 'dripline-plugin-aws' }
- `git:github.com/user/repo@v1` → { type: 'git', url: 'https://github.com/user/repo.git', ref: 'v1' }
- `https://github.com/user/repo` → { type: 'git', url: 'https://github.com/user/repo.git' }
- `./path/to/plugin` → { type: 'local', path: resolved absolute path }
- `/absolute/path` → { type: 'local', path: '/absolute/path' }

`installPlugin(source: string, options?: { global?: boolean }): Promise<{ path: string, name: string }>` — install a plugin:
- npm: run `npm install <name>@<ref>` in the plugins dir. For global: `~/.dripline/plugins/npm/`. For project: `.dripline/plugins/npm/`.
- git: `git clone <url>` into plugins dir. For global: `~/.dripline/plugins/git/<host>/<path>/`. Run `npm install` if package.json exists.
- local: just validate the path exists, add to config.

`removePlugin(name: string): boolean` — remove from installed list and delete files.

`listInstalled(): Array<{ name: string, type: string, version?: string, path: string }>` — read installed plugins from `.dripline/plugins.json`.

The plugins.json format:
```json
{
  "plugins": [
    { "source": "npm:@dripline/github@1.0.0", "path": "./plugins/npm/@dripline/github" },
    { "source": "git:github.com/user/repo", "path": "./plugins/git/github.com/user/repo" },
    { "source": "./my-plugin.ts", "path": "/abs/path/my-plugin.ts" }
  ]
}
```

Use execSync for npm/git commands. Handle errors gracefully.

